headline: The Dow Is Getting Pummeled by UnitedHealth. Why the Rest of the Stock Market Is Fine.
summary: Just look at  UnitedHealth  The Dow tumbled more than 500 points, or 1%, in early trading Tuesday before rebounding a bit.  UnitedHealth, which reported earnings Tuesday morning, was hit by weaker-than-expected revenue and underwhelming guidance for 2026.  News late Monday that the Trump administration was proposing a smaller-than-forecast increase in Medicare Advantage reimbursements only served to make investors even more nervous.

headline: Are Wall Street Analysts Bullish on Cisco Systems Stock?
summary: As Cisco Systems has outperformed the broader market over the past 52 weeks, Wall Street analysts maintain a moderately optimistic outlook about the stock’s prospects.

headline: Does Georgetown’s Wi‑Fi 7 Overhaul With Cisco (CSCO) Redefine Its Campus AI Networking Edge?
summary: Cisco announced in January 2026 that it will power a multi-year modernization of Georgetown University’s campus network, including one of higher education’s largest Wi‑Fi 7 rollouts across classrooms, dorms, stadiums, and research facilities. By combining high-density Wi‑Fi 7 infrastructure, campus-wide security, and AI-ready networking analytics, the partnership turns Georgetown into a live showcase for Cisco’s next-generation connectivity and data capabilities. headline: Alkira Appoints S&P Global's Guru Ramamoorthy to Advisory Board to Accelerate AI-Native Networking Strategy
summary: Alkira, the leader in Network Infrastructure as a Service (NIaaS), today announced the appointment of Guru Ramamoorthy, Global Head of Cloud & Infrastructure at S&P Global, to its advisory board. Ramamoorthy's appointment further strengthens Alkira's leadership with a proven executive who understands the complexities of modern enterprise infrastructure.
